The paper proposes a novel framework for optimizing the latent representations of entities and relations in large knowledge graphs, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the scalability and computational efficiency of the proposed method, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The paper uses natural language processing techniques to formulate the learning objective, which is relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
